headline: Earnings to watch this week: Dollar Tree, Broadcom, Figma
summary: Yahoo Finance Senior Business Reporter Ines Ferré takes a look at the biggest quarterly earnings results out this week, starting on Wednesday, Sept. 3. Dollar Tree (DLTR) reports its second quarter results on Wednesday before markets open. Analysts expect $4.4 billion in revenue and $0.46 in adjusted earnings per share (EPS). After markets close, Figma (FIG) will also announce its second quarter results, just about a month after the company's initial public offering (IPO). Broadcom's (AVGO) third quarter results are out on Thursday after markets close. Analysts anticipate $15.8 billion in revenue and $1.67 in adjusted EPS. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination.
